      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HIGHLY POTENT (1) is an honest type who is new here. Had a squeeze draw but was too good last time scoring by 1.3 lengths at Warragul over 460m (25.89). Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. The one to beat again. TRIPPED OUT (3) finished in the minors last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 525m at The Meadows, taking a Mix 6/7 in a speedy 30.01. Expected to feature on best figures. CONCEIVABLE (5) looks close to win after hitting the frame last run (29.93) at this track in a Mix 6/7. Has first look at box 5 this time. Has never been out of the money in three starts this course and distance. Can feature again. CRACKERJACK GAZ (7) is a last-start placegetter in a fast-run race - should be thereabouts.",
